   594	   2. `docker build` against repo root succeeds; image runs each
   595	      service module under a smoke `--help` invocation.
   596	3. **Compose service entries**.
   597	   1. Wire all six EDEN services + the bare-repo init service.
   598	   2. `docker compose up --wait` brings the whole stack online.
   599	4. **setup-experiment script**.
   600	   1. Wire the script.
   601	   2. End-to-end: `setup-experiment.sh && docker compose up
   602	      --wait` runs the fixture experiment to quiescence.
   603	5. **Smoke + CI extension**.
   604	   1. Extend `smoke.sh` with the new assertions.
   605	   2. Add `python-test-postgres` job.
   606	6. **Documentation refresh**.
   607	
   608	If implementation runs over context, stop at the next **chunk-internal
   609	milestone** boundary — never mid-milestone.
   610	
   611	## Out of scope
   612	
   613	- **Gitea integration** as the workers' actual git remote (deferred
   614	  to a follow-up sub-chunk after 10d).
   615	- **Experiment-specific images** for the LLM implementer's sandbox
   616	  (10d).
   617	- **Control-plane registration** (Phase 12).
   618	- **Postgres connection pooling** (single connection per store
   619	  instance is fine for one orchestrator + one task-store-server).
   620	- **Multi-replica orchestrator coordination** (Phase 12).
   621	- **Resource limits** on Compose services (10d when LLM workers
   622	  introduce real cost).
   623	- **Branch-protection update** to require the new
   624	  `python-test-postgres` job — defer to a follow-up after a few
   625	  clean runs (same posture 10a took for `compose-smoke`).
   626	
   627	## Risks / things to watch
   628	
   629	- **`uv sync --frozen` in Docker requires `uv.lock`.** If the lock
   630	  file ever becomes stale relative to `pyproject.toml`, `--frozen`
   631	  fails the build. We commit `uv.lock`; the existing `python-lint`
   632	  / `python-typecheck` / `python-test` jobs all use `--frozen`
   633	  successfully, so this is consistent with current discipline.
   634	
   635	- **`postgres:16.6-alpine` image hash.** 10a pinned the major.minor;
   636	  we should consider pinning the digest in CI for absolute
   637	  determinism. Currently we don't — out of scope for this chunk.
   638	
   639	- **Compose `configs:` vs bind-mounting the experiment-config
   640	  YAML.** Compose configs are nicer (immutable, declared centrally)
   641	  but only work in Swarm or a recent-enough Compose v2. The
   642	  fallback is a `volumes:` entry mounting the file. Verify whether
   643	  CI's Compose version supports `configs:` in non-Swarm mode; if
   644	  not, fall back to a regular bind-mount. (Compose v2.20+ supports
   645	  it; CI's `ubuntu-latest` ships v2.27+; should be fine.)
   646	
   647	- **psycopg's binary wheel availability on Linux/arm64.** Most
   648	  platforms have wheels for `psycopg[binary]>=3.2`; if a CI runner
   649	  doesn't, fall back to building from source — adds ~30s to image
   650	  build. Acceptable.
   651	
   652	- **Image bloat.** The shared image will be ~400MB (Python slim +
   653	  workspace + git). If this becomes problematic later, multi-stage
   654	  with a `wheels` builder is the standard fix; not needed yet.
   655	
   656	- **The web-ui's `--repo-path` flag.** The web-ui needs the bare
   657	  repo for the work-refs admin sub-page. We mount it. The flag
   658	  also gates the entire implementer module (chunk 9c), which the
   659	  scripted implementer-host service makes redundant — both modules
   660	  now race for the same tasks. **In Compose**, only the
   661	  implementer-host should claim implement tasks; the web-ui's
   662	  implementer module is for human override / debugging. We keep
   663	  both available; the user opens whichever they prefer. Document
   664	  this in the compose README.

